"Sampei Y., Matsumoto E., Tokuoka T., Inoue D.","Changes in accumulation rate of organic carbon during the last 8,000 years in sediments of Nakaumi Lagoon, Japan",1997,"Marine Chemistry","58","1-2",,"39","50",,,10.1016/S0304-4203(97)00024-8,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0031438189&partnerID=40&md5=07d8ab14c27f5a027ccf6d8349dcd7d0","Department of Geoscience, Faculty of Science and Engineering, Shimane University, 1060 Nishikawatsu Matsue, Shimane 690, Japan; Inst. for Hydrospheric-Atmosph. Sci., Nagoya University, Furo-cho, Chikusa-ku, Nagoya 464-01, Japan; Abiko Research Laboratory CRIEPI, 1646 Abiko, Abiko 270-11, Japan","Sampei, Y., Department of Geoscience, Faculty of Science and Engineering, Shimane University, 1060 Nishikawatsu Matsue, Shimane 690, Japan; Matsumoto, E., Inst. for Hydrospheric-Atmosph. Sci., Nagoya University, Furo-cho, Chikusa-ku, Nagoya 464-01, Japan; Tokuoka, T., Department of Geoscience, Faculty of Science and Engineering, Shimane University, 1060 Nishikawatsu Matsue, Shimane 690, Japan; Inoue, D., Abiko Research Laboratory CRIEPI, 1646 Abiko, Abiko 270-11, Japan","Changes in the organic carbon accumulation rate (C(org) A.R.) and their relation to climate changes during the last 8,000 years were investigated in a 20 m sediment core from the Nakaumi Lagoon, southwest Japan. High-resolution 14C dating was possible from fifteen shell samples. The warm climate interval 8,000-6.500 cal. yr B.P. was accompanied by an increase in the C(org) A.R. (21-32 g m-2 yr-1) and the cool climate interval 3,000-2,000 cal. yr B.P. by a decrease (11 g m-2 yr-1). The accumulation of both terrestrial and planktonic organic matter increased during the warm interval. The lagoon seems to act as a more effective small sink for atmospheric CO2 following the global warming climate.","Climate; Lagoon; Organic carbon accumulation rate; Organic carbon content","climate change; coastal lagoons; Holocene; lagoonal sedimentation; organic carbon; Japan, Honshu, Nakaumi Lagoon",,,,,,"An, Z.S., Kukla, G.J., Porter, S.C., Xiao, J., Magnetic susceptibility evidence of monsoon variation on the Loess Plateau of Central China during the last 130,000 years (1991) Quat. Res., 36, pp. 29-36; Arai, F., Oba, T., Kitazato, H., Horibe, Y., Machida, H., Late quaternary tephro chronology and paleo-oceanography of the sediments of the Japan sea (1981) The Quaternary Research, 20, pp. 209-230. , Jpn. Assoc. Quat. Res. (in Japanese with English abstract); Bard, E., Hamelin, B., Fairbanks, R.G., Zindler, A., Calibration of the 14C timescale over the past 30,000 years using mass spectrometric U-Th ages from Barbados corals (1990) Nature, 345, pp. 405-410; Biggs, R.B., Sharp, J.H., Church, T.M., Tramontano, J.M., Optical properties, suspended sediments and chemistry associated with the turbidity maxima of the Delaware Estuary (1983) Can. J. Fish. Aq. Sci., 40, pp. 172-179; Bordowskiy, O.K., Source of organic matter in marine basins (1965) Mar. Geol., 3, pp. 5-31; Bowman, S., Radiocarbon concentration effects (1990) Radiocarbon Dating, pp. 16-30. , Br. Mus. Publ; Bryson, R.A., Swain, A.M., Holocene variations of monsoon rainfall in Rajasthan (1981) Quat. Res., 16, pp. 135-145; Burney, D.A., Late Holocene environmental changes in arid southwestern Madagascar (1993) Quat. Res., 40, pp. 98-106; Calvert, S.E., Pedersen, T.F., Organic carbon accumulation and preservation in marine sediments: How important is anoxia? (1992) Organic Matter: Productivity, Accumulation and Preservation in Recent and Ancient Sediments, pp. 231-263. , Whelan, J., Farrington, J.W. (Eds.). Columbia Press; Climatic change of the last 18,000 years: Observations and model simulations (1988) Science, 241, pp. 1043-1052. , COHMAP Members; Damon, P.E., Linick, T.W., Geomagnetic-heliomagnetic modulation of atmospheric radiocarbon production (1986) Radiocarbon, 28, pp. 266-278; Damon, P.E., Cheng, S., Linick, T.W., Fine and hyperfine structure in the spectrum of secular varia